CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Vehicle Laws – Stopping, Standing, or Parking in a Bike Lane or Bicycle Path –
3 Prohibition
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting a person from stopping, standing, or parking a vehicle in a
5 bike lane or bicycle path, subject to certain exceptions; and generally relating to
6 stopping, standing, or parking a vehicle in a bike lane or bicycle path.
7 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
8 Article – Transportation
9 Section 21–101(a), (c), and (e) and 21–1003(a)
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
12 BY adding to
13 Article – Transportation
14 Section 21–1003(gg)
15 Annotated Code of Maryland
16 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
17 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
18 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
19 Article – Transportation
20 21–101.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
